  "title": "Uncaught TypeError: y is not a function - bundled version of preact@10.0.5 errors when executing code compiled with Webpack",
  "body": "**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nWe just upgraded InstantSearch from 3.x to 4.0.1 and have everything working great...except in production where our code is compiled _and minified_ using Webpack with Terser.\r\n\r\nWhen using `search.addWidgets([...])`, instantsearch invokes `preact` code which causes the TypeError shown below.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22938/70348832-c2890080-1820-11ea-9aad-2189bddc6217.png)\r\n\r\nDon't ask me why but downgrading to exactly `preact@10.0.1` makes the issue go away.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. instantsearch@4.0.1, preact@10.0.5 (or really any version > 10.0.1)\r\n2. Compile code with gulp webpack-stream 5.2.1 using latest Terser plugin minimizer with default settings\r\n3. Use `search.addWidgets` (need to be at least 1 `refinementList` widget) to trigger preact code\r\n4. Load page",
